Find the minimum Hamming weight (popcount) of the set {popcount(2023 * n) | n ∈ ℤ⁺}. Note that 2023 = 7 * 17^2. A Hamming weight of 1 is impossible because 2023 is not a power of 2. Check if a Hamming weight of 2 is possible by checking if there exist integers a, b such that 2^a + 2^b ≡ 0 (mod 2023) or 2^a ≡ -2^b (mod 2023). This is equivalent to checking if -1 is in the subgroup generated by 2 modulo 2023, or more simply, if there exists an integer k such that 2^k ≡ -1 (mod 2023) or if 2^a ≡ 2^b (mod 2023) can be manipulated. Actually, the condition for popcount(2023*n) = 2 is that 2^a + 2^b is a multiple of 2023 for some a, b. This is equivalent to 2^{a-b} ≡ -1 (mod 2023) if we assume a > b. If no such a, b exist, check for popcount 3, etc. Use the property that 2^k mod 2023 will eventually repeat.
